headline: Does Williams-Sonoma (WSM) Still Offer Value After Its Strong Multi‑Year Share Price Run?
summary: If you have been wondering whether Williams-Sonoma's share price still reflects fair value after its recent run, you are not alone. The stock last closed at US$197.81, with returns of 10.8% over 7 days, 9.6% over 30 days, 5.3% year to date, 3.2% over 1 year, 225.9% over 3 years and 247.8% over 5 years, which naturally raises questions about what is already priced in. headline: Why 2026 Could Be the Year Mid-Cap Value Dividend Stocks Finally Win
summary: Large-cap growth stocks have dominated for so long because most investors have stopped looking at anything else. The thinking here is pretty simple in that why would you bother with mid-caps or small-caps when you can own the Magnificent Seven and watch your portfolio compound by double digits annually.
